<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1701,2017]" box="[151,997,1701,1729]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1701,1728]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Dimensions</emphasis>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Salle, A." box="[456,596,1701,1728]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" pagination="429 - 435" refId="ref21411" refString="Salle, A. (1850) Coleopteres nouveaux de l'Amerique. 2 e partie. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 7 (2), 429 - 435." type="journal article" year="1850">Sallé (1850)</bibRefCitation>
, length 
<quantity box="[685,794,1702,1729]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="9.0">9–19 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[876,993,1701,1729]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1701,2017]" box="[199,1379,1737,1765]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1737,1764]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salle" authorityYear="1850" box="[359,603,1738,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[359,603,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Pteroplatus variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[780,895,1738,1764]" name="Venezuela" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Salle, A." box="[910,1032,1737,1764]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" pagination="429 - 435" refId="ref21411" refString="Salle, A. (1850) Coleopteres nouveaux de l'Amerique. 2 e partie. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 7 (2), 429 - 435." type="journal article" year="1850">Sallé 1850</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1094,1204,1738,1764]" name="Colombia" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[1219,1366,1738,1765]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" pagination="279 - 296" refId="ref21273" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) List of the Longicornia collected by the late Mr. P. Bouchard, at Santa Marta. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1866, 279 - 296. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1967. tb 01436. x" type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe 1866</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1701,2017]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,268,1774,1800]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Types</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salle" authorityYear="1850" box="[282,525,1774,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[282,525,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Pteroplatus variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on 
<typeStatus box="[799,897,1775,1801]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">syntypes</typeStatus>
(gender and number of specimens examined not indicated), deposited at MNHN.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1701,2017]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1846,1872]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Remarks</emphasis>
. We did not examine specimens of this species. However, as in all species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buquet" authorityYear="1840" box="[1170,1300,1846,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1170,1300,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Pteroplatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the color is variable, especially on the elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1701,2017]" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salle" authorityYear="1850" box="[199,444,1918,1944]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pteroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[199,444,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Pteroplatus variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the species without small gibbosities on the distal area of the elytra, which is only slightly widened from the midlength. The tuft of long setae of the antennomeres III–V is distinct only on distal third or quarter.
</paragraph>
